- Average temperature is a key indicator of climate trends; 
- A gap of at least 2 years between the first and second records may indicate data collection consistency and reliability; 
- The threshold of 10 degrees Celsius may be used to differentiate between colder and warmer climates.

sql:
SELECT year, MAX(avg_temp) AS highest_avg_temp
FROM weather_data
GROUP BY year;
